  "text": "The embedded model, which consists of M, D and of the noise estimator L, constitutes the state predictor of the plant and disturbance. It is called the \"state predictor\", since it forecasts the state at the next time step using the current state and input values of each DT integrator (Σ block). The loop from the M output port back to the M input port, passing through L and D is the Predictor Loop (PL). The main input and output of the PL are the sensor measurement y, the predicted outputŷ m and the prediction errorê m = y m −ŷ m . The performance of the state predictor is mainly described byê m , whose relation to the model error e m = y − y m and to the equivalent disturbance d y according to the EMC theory [CITATION_1] is:ê",
